reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 9, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Excellent bag! Fits Microsoft Surface Studio laptop
reviews.reviewText: I'm really pleased with this case! It looks nice, has solid construction, and fits my Microsoft Surface Studio laptop and accessories perfectly. The power supply/cord fits in the lower right outside pocket, my USB hub fits in the top right outside pocket, and my external mouse, tablet shortcut remote, and drawing glove all fit together in the flap pocket. I can also add a sketchbook in the full-width zipper pocket, my Kindle in one of the inside pockets, and a spare charging cable or two without straining the zipper.The case itself is lightweight, with a sturdy shoulder strap that's long enough to carry cross-body if desired. The whole thing is compact enough to slide into an outer pocket of my airline carry-on bag, and can then be pulled out and tucked under the seat in front of me for in-flight use while the larger carry-on is in the overhead compartment.If you have a Surface Studio Laptop or comparable device and need a practical slim case, do recommend!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 26, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Bought it for our daughter's chromebook. Very nice bag. It zips up end to end to keep it protected. Padded for protection yet not bulky at all. Pockets for extra storage. I'd buy it again!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 4, 2023
reviews.reviewText: This case is great. It has a lot of hidden pockets and it can hold so so many different things. It has enough sizable pockets for me to carry my m3 pro MacBook laptop, a 11 inch tablet, and 2 different cells phones all at the same time and still have room to store ink pens, paperwork, and the chargers to each item. I love it and I do not regret buying it. Very helpful for protecting the laptop, tablet, and other electronics from the dirt, rain, and spills.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 14, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Nice bag for price
reviews.reviewText: I like this bag. It fits my computer and the pockets on front are perfect for my accessories. It is thin and sturdy. My laptop (13 inch) fits perfect even with a neoprene sleeve I have.The cons, the pockets are uneven and look kind of cheap because of that. Not like pictured. I imagine I could have exchanged it, but I needed it for work. They still function and the bag is otherwise well built and padded. When I put my reeled cable in for my laptop, it is a bit bulgy but that isn’t a deal breaker. I also keep my computer in a sleeve in this bag and I know if I didn’t, it would be less bulky. This is perfect if your chargers all fit in the front pockets. The other con is I don’t like Velcro and the long pocket is Velcro. It isn’t a deal breaker. I put pens in there so I’m not worried about things falling out. The inner pocket is very thin and tight but you can put your phone, keys, pens, and even a small folder in it. So it is roomy.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 9, 2024
reviews.reviewText: Love the pockets! I have space for my laptop (14inch) and my iPad (12.9inch) a notebook and a folder. It’s nice and slim, I love the strap I just throw it across my body and go!!I got it in teal ,it’s very cute!!I’m sure the other colors are just as vibrant! The color pops!
